COLORADO SPRINGS, Thursday, Dec. 7 (AP)--Spencer Penrose, Colorado Springs mining financier and builder of Broadmoor Hotel, died at 12:50 A.M. today. He had been suffering from a throat ailment. His age was 74. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
